<p>Herein, the relative movement between the diamond tool and workpiece surface in the height direction, i.e., the infeed direction is expressed as a mono-frequency harmonic equation corresponding to the phase shift [
 <xref rid="B73-micromachines-10-00288" ref-type="bibr">73</xref>] 
 <disp-formula id="FD8-micromachines-10-00288">
  <label>(8)</label>
  <math id="mm16">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>z</mi>
      <mi mathvariant="normal">v</mi>
     </msub>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mi>t</mi>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mi>A</mi>
     <mi>sin</mi>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mrow>
       <mn>2</mn>
       <mi>π</mi>
       <msub>
        <mi>f</mi>
        <mi>z</mi>
       </msub>
       <mi>t</mi>
       <mo>−</mo>
       <mi>ϕ</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> where 
 <italic>A</italic> is the amplitude of the mono-frequency vibration. Furthermore, the tool locus projected on the 
 <italic>x-z</italic> plane (the feed direction is always configured as the 
 <italic>x</italic>-axis) can be expressed as in terms of the phase shift (
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm17">
   <mrow>
    <mi>ϕ</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>) and feed rate (
 <italic>f</italic>) as [
 <xref rid="B74-micromachines-10-00288" ref-type="bibr">74</xref>] 
 <disp-formula id="FD9-micromachines-10-00288">
  <label>(9)</label>
  <math id="mm18">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>z</mi>
      <mi>f</mi>
     </msub>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mi>x</mi>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mi>A</mi>
     <mrow>
      <mo>[</mo>
      <mrow>
       <mn>1</mn>
       <mo>−</mo>
       <mi>cos</mi>
       <mrow>
        <mo>(</mo>
        <mrow>
         <mfrac>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mi>f</mi>
         </mfrac>
         <mi>ϕ</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mo>)</mo>
       </mrow>
      </mrow>
      <mo>]</mo>
     </mrow>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>
</p>
